Process called "sha256_compress_block" takes state_buffer as Integer, block_buffer as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Processes one 64-byte block by the SHA-256 message schedule and 64-round
    compression function. State is 8 x 32-bit working variables h0..h7 stored
    as 8 x 8-byte qwords in state_buffer (high bytes zero - we keep them in
    32-bit form). block_buffer is exactly 64 bytes.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Per FIPS 180-4 section 6.2.2:
    1. Build W[0..63]: W[i] = block big-endian u32 for i<16,
       W[i] = sigma1(W[i-2]) + W[i-7] + sigma0(W[i-15]) + W[i-16] for i>=16.
    2. Initialize working variables a..h from state.
    3. For each of 64 rounds: T1, T2, shift the working window.
    4. Add the working window back into the state.
    @End Implementation

    Let mask be 4294967295

    Note: Build W[0..15] from block bytes (big-endian)
    Let W_buffer_size be 64 multiplied by 8
    Note: Use 64 8-byte qwords on stack via a small arena pattern: we re-use
    Note: the trailing portion of state_buffer would conflict, so we allocate
    Note: from a side scratch area provided as part of the API contract.
    Note: To keep this routine self-contained we allocate W on the caller's
    Note: arena. We approximate that by writing W into block_buffer's tail
    Note: extension - sha256 callers always pass a 512-byte scratch (W array
    Note: + reserved tail) per the SHA256 context layout.
    Note: For simplicity here, we use 8 byte * 64 entries = 512 bytes of W
    Note: stored at block_buffer + 64 (caller guarantees this is available).

    Let W_base be block_buffer plus 64

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than 16:
        Let b0 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with block_buffer, i multiplied by 4
        Let b1 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with block_buffer, i multiplied by 4 plus 1
        Let b2 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with block_buffer, i multiplied by 4 plus 2
        Let b3 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with block_buffer, i multiplied by 4 plus 3
        Let word_value be b0 multiplied by 16777216 plus b1 multiplied by 65536 plus b2 multiplied by 256 plus b3
        proc memory_set_qword from Memory with W_base, i multiplied by 8, word_value
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Set i to 16
    While i is less than 64:
        Let w_im2 be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with W_base, (i minus 2) multiplied by 8
        Let w_im7 be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with W_base, (i minus 7) multiplied by 8
        Let w_im15 be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with W_base, (i minus 15) multiplied by 8
        Let w_im16 be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with W_base, (i minus 16) multiplied by 8

        Let s1_a be proc rotr32 with w_im2, 17
        Let s1_b be proc rotr32 with w_im2, 19
        Let s1_c be proc shr32 with w_im2, 10
        Let sigma1 be s1_a bitwise_xor s1_b
        Set sigma1 to sigma1 bitwise_xor s1_c

        Let s0_a be proc rotr32 with w_im15, 7
        Let s0_b be proc rotr32 with w_im15, 18
        Let s0_c be proc shr32 with w_im15, 3
        Let sigma0 be s0_a bitwise_xor s0_b
        Set sigma0 to sigma0 bitwise_xor s0_c

        Let new_w be proc u32_add with sigma1, w_im7
        Set new_w to proc u32_add with new_w, sigma0
        Set new_w to proc u32_add with new_w, w_im16
        proc memory_set_qword from Memory with W_base, i multiplied by 8, new_w
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Load working window a..h
    Let a be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 0
    Let b be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 8
    Let c be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 16
    Let d be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 24
    Let e be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 32
    Let f be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 40
    Let g be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 48
    Let h be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 56

    Set i to 0
    While i is less than 64:
        Let big_sigma1_a be proc rotr32 with e, 6
        Let big_sigma1_b be proc rotr32 with e, 11
        Let big_sigma1_c be proc rotr32 with e, 25
        Let big_sigma1 be big_sigma1_a bitwise_xor big_sigma1_b
        Set big_sigma1 to big_sigma1 bitwise_xor big_sigma1_c

        Let ch_e_f be e bitwise_and f
        Let not_e be e bitwise_xor mask
        Let ch_ne_g be not_e bitwise_and g
        Let ch be ch_e_f bitwise_xor ch_ne_g

        Let k_value be proc sha256_k_constant with i
        Let w_value be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with W_base, i multiplied by 8

        Let t1 be proc u32_add with h, big_sigma1
        Set t1 to proc u32_add with t1, ch
        Set t1 to proc u32_add with t1, k_value
        Set t1 to proc u32_add with t1, w_value

        Let big_sigma0_a be proc rotr32 with a, 2
        Let big_sigma0_b be proc rotr32 with a, 13
        Let big_sigma0_c be proc rotr32 with a, 22
        Let big_sigma0 be big_sigma0_a bitwise_xor big_sigma0_b
        Set big_sigma0 to big_sigma0 bitwise_xor big_sigma0_c

        Let maj_a_b be a bitwise_and b
        Let maj_a_c be a bitwise_and c
        Let maj_b_c be b bitwise_and c
        Let maj be maj_a_b bitwise_xor maj_a_c
        Set maj to maj bitwise_xor maj_b_c

        Let t2 be proc u32_add with big_sigma0, maj

        Set h to g
        Set g to f
        Set f to e
        Set e to proc u32_add with d, t1
        Set d to c
        Set c to b
        Set b to a
        Set a to proc u32_add with t1, t2
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Add working window back into the state
    Let h0 be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 0
    Let h1 be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 8
    Let h2 be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 16
    Let h3 be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 24
    Let h4 be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 32
    Let h5 be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 40
    Let h6 be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 48
    Let h7 be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 56

    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 0, proc u32_add with h0, a
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 8, proc u32_add with h1, b
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 16, proc u32_add with h2, c
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 24, proc u32_add with h3, d
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 32, proc u32_add with h4, e
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 40, proc u32_add with h5, f
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 48, proc u32_add with h6, g
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 56, proc u32_add with h7, h

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "sha256_hash" takes arena as Integer, message as Integer, message_length as Integer, out_digest as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Computes the SHA-256 hash of message[0..message_length) into out_digest
    (caller must provide 32 bytes). One-shot interface; for streaming use
    sha256_init + sha256_update + sha256_final (not exposed here as RSA/X.509
    signature verification always has the full TBS bytes in memory).
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Allocate scratch space: state (8 qwords = 64 bytes) + block (64 bytes)
       + W (512 bytes) + padded message buffer.
    2. Initialize state with FIPS H_0 constants.
    3. Pad the message per FIPS 180-4 5.1.1: append 0x80, k zero bytes such
       that (length+1+k) mod 64 == 56, then 8 bytes of bit-length big-endian.
    4. Walk padded message 64 bytes at a time through sha256_compress_block.
    5. Serialize state h0..h7 as big-endian into out_digest.
    @End Implementation

    Let scratch_size be 64 plus 64 plus 512
    Let state_buffer be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, scratch_size
    If state_buffer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let block_buffer be state_buffer plus 64

    Note: Initial hash values (FIPS 180-4 5.3.3): first 32 bits of fractional
    Note: parts of square roots of first 8 primes.
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 0, 1779033703
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 8, 3144134277
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 16, 1013904242
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 24, 2773480762
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 32, 1359893119
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 40, 2600822924
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 48, 528734635
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 56, 1541459225

    Note: Process all complete 64-byte blocks
    Let full_blocks be message_length divided by 64
    Let processed be 0
    While processed is less than full_blocks:
        Let copy_idx be 0
        While copy_idx is less than 64:
            Let src_byte be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with message, processed multiplied by 64 plus copy_idx
            proc memory_set_byte from Memory with block_buffer, copy_idx, src_byte
            Set copy_idx to copy_idx plus 1
        End While
        proc sha256_compress_block with state_buffer, block_buffer
        Set processed to processed plus 1
    End While

    Note: Handle final partial block + padding
    Let tail_offset be full_blocks multiplied by 64
    Let tail_bytes be message_length minus tail_offset

    Note: Copy remaining bytes into block_buffer
    Let tail_i be 0
    While tail_i is less than tail_bytes:
        Let src_b be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with message, tail_offset plus tail_i
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with block_buffer, tail_i, src_b
        Set tail_i to tail_i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Append 0x80
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with block_buffer, tail_bytes, 128
    Let pad_pos be tail_bytes plus 1

    Note: Zero-fill. If we cannot fit length suffix (need pad_pos <= 56),
    Note: we must produce two blocks.
    If pad_pos is greater than 56:
        Let zero_idx be pad_pos
        While zero_idx is less than 64:
            proc memory_set_byte from Memory with block_buffer, zero_idx, 0
            Set zero_idx to zero_idx plus 1
        End While
        proc sha256_compress_block with state_buffer, block_buffer
        Let z2 be 0
        While z2 is less than 56:
            proc memory_set_byte from Memory with block_buffer, z2, 0
            Set z2 to z2 plus 1
        End While
    Otherwise:
        Let z_inner be pad_pos
        While z_inner is less than 56:
            proc memory_set_byte from Memory with block_buffer, z_inner, 0
            Set z_inner to z_inner plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Note: Append 64-bit length (bits) big-endian into bytes 56..63
    Let bit_length be message_length multiplied by 8
    Let bb_i be 7
    While bb_i is greater than 0 minus 1:
        Let byte_value be bit_length modulo by 256
        Set bit_length to bit_length divided by 256
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with block_buffer, 56 plus bb_i, byte_value
        Set bb_i to bb_i minus 1
    End While

    proc sha256_compress_block with state_buffer, block_buffer

    Note: Serialize 8 state words as big-endian into out_digest
    Let state_word_index be 0
    While state_word_index is less than 8:
        Let state_word be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, state_word_index multiplied by 8
        Let byte_idx be 3
        While byte_idx is greater than 0 minus 1:
            Let byte_val be state_word modulo by 256
            Set state_word to state_word divided by 256
            proc memory_set_byte from Memory with out_digest, state_word_index multiplied by 4 plus byte_idx, byte_val
            Set byte_idx to byte_idx minus 1
        End While
        Set state_word_index to state_word_index plus 1
    End While

    Return 32
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SHA-384 / SHA-512 (64-bit operations)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "sha512_k_constant" takes index as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    The 80 round constants K_0..K_79 for SHA-384/512, the first 64 bits of
    the fractional parts of the cube roots of the first 80 primes. Same
    case-based access pattern as sha256_k_constant.
    @End Reasoning

    Note: K constants verified against FIPS 180-4 5.3.5. Each is the first
    Note: 64 bits of the fractional parts of the cube roots of the first 80
    Note: primes, encoded as signed two's-complement int64 (negative when
    Note: the high bit is set).
