Process called "sha512_compress_block" takes state_buffer as Integer, block_buffer as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Processes one 128-byte block by SHA-512's message schedule and 80-round
    compression function. State is 8 x 64-bit working variables. Block is
    128 bytes. We expand to 80 64-bit W values in a scratch area at
    block_buffer + 128.
    @End Reasoning

    Let W_base be block_buffer plus 128

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than 16:
        Let w_acc be 0
        Let byte_in be 0
        While byte_in is less than 8:
            Set w_acc to w_acc multiplied by 256
            Let bv be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with block_buffer, i multiplied by 8 plus byte_in
            Set w_acc to w_acc plus bv
            Set byte_in to byte_in plus 1
        End While
        proc memory_set_qword from Memory with W_base, i multiplied by 8, w_acc
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Set i to 16
    While i is less than 80:
        Let w_im2 be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with W_base, (i minus 2) multiplied by 8
        Let w_im7 be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with W_base, (i minus 7) multiplied by 8
        Let w_im15 be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with W_base, (i minus 15) multiplied by 8
        Let w_im16 be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with W_base, (i minus 16) multiplied by 8

        Let s1_a be proc rotr64 with w_im2, 19
        Let s1_b be proc rotr64 with w_im2, 61
        Let s1_c be proc shr64 with w_im2, 6
        Let sigma1 be s1_a bitwise_xor s1_b
        Set sigma1 to sigma1 bitwise_xor s1_c

        Let s0_a be proc rotr64 with w_im15, 1
        Let s0_b be proc rotr64 with w_im15, 8
        Let s0_c be proc shr64 with w_im15, 7
        Let sigma0 be s0_a bitwise_xor s0_b
        Set sigma0 to sigma0 bitwise_xor s0_c

        Let new_w be sigma1 plus w_im7
        Set new_w to new_w plus sigma0
        Set new_w to new_w plus w_im16
        proc memory_set_qword from Memory with W_base, i multiplied by 8, new_w
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Let a be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 0
    Let b be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 8
    Let c be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 16
    Let d be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 24
    Let e be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 32
    Let f be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 40
    Let g be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 48
    Let h be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 56

    Set i to 0
    While i is less than 80:
        Let big_sigma1_a be proc rotr64 with e, 14
        Let big_sigma1_b be proc rotr64 with e, 18
        Let big_sigma1_c be proc rotr64 with e, 41
        Let big_sigma1 be big_sigma1_a bitwise_xor big_sigma1_b
        Set big_sigma1 to big_sigma1 bitwise_xor big_sigma1_c

        Let ch_e_f be e bitwise_and f
        Let not_e be e bitwise_xor (0 minus 1)
        Let ch_ne_g be not_e bitwise_and g
        Let ch be ch_e_f bitwise_xor ch_ne_g

        Let k_value be proc sha512_k_constant with i
        Let w_value be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with W_base, i multiplied by 8

        Let t1 be h plus big_sigma1
        Set t1 to t1 plus ch
        Set t1 to t1 plus k_value
        Set t1 to t1 plus w_value

        Let big_sigma0_a be proc rotr64 with a, 28
        Let big_sigma0_b be proc rotr64 with a, 34
        Let big_sigma0_c be proc rotr64 with a, 39
        Let big_sigma0 be big_sigma0_a bitwise_xor big_sigma0_b
        Set big_sigma0 to big_sigma0 bitwise_xor big_sigma0_c

        Let maj_a_b be a bitwise_and b
        Let maj_a_c be a bitwise_and c
        Let maj_b_c be b bitwise_and c
        Let maj be maj_a_b bitwise_xor maj_a_c
        Set maj to maj bitwise_xor maj_b_c

        Let t2 be big_sigma0 plus maj

        Set h to g
        Set g to f
        Set f to e
        Set e to d plus t1
        Set d to c
        Set c to b
        Set b to a
        Set a to t1 plus t2
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Let h0 be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 0
    Let h1 be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 8
    Let h2 be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 16
    Let h3 be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 24
    Let h4 be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 32
    Let h5 be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 40
    Let h6 be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 48
    Let h7 be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 56

    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 0, h0 plus a
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 8, h1 plus b
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 16, h2 plus c
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 24, h3 plus d
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 32, h4 plus e
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 40, h5 plus f
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 48, h6 plus g
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 56, h7 plus h

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "sha512_hash_with_iv" takes arena as Integer, message as Integer, message_length as Integer, out_digest as Integer, out_size as Integer, iv0 as Integer, iv1 as Integer, iv2 as Integer, iv3 as Integer, iv4 as Integer, iv5 as Integer, iv6 as Integer, iv7 as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Shared SHA-384 / SHA-512 driver, parameterized by the initial hash
    values. The only differences between SHA-384 and SHA-512 are the IV and
    the truncation of the output: SHA-384 takes the first 48 of 64 bytes.
    @End Reasoning

    Let scratch_size be 64 plus 128 plus 640
    Let state_buffer be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, scratch_size
    If state_buffer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let block_buffer be state_buffer plus 64

    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 0, iv0
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 8, iv1
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 16, iv2
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 24, iv3
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 32, iv4
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 40, iv5
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 48, iv6
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with state_buffer, 56, iv7

    Let full_blocks be message_length divided by 128
    Let processed be 0
    While processed is less than full_blocks:
        Let copy_idx be 0
        While copy_idx is less than 128:
            Let src_byte be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with message, processed multiplied by 128 plus copy_idx
            proc memory_set_byte from Memory with block_buffer, copy_idx, src_byte
            Set copy_idx to copy_idx plus 1
        End While
        proc sha512_compress_block with state_buffer, block_buffer
        Set processed to processed plus 1
    End While

    Let tail_offset be full_blocks multiplied by 128
    Let tail_bytes be message_length minus tail_offset

    Let tail_i be 0
    While tail_i is less than tail_bytes:
        Let src_b be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with message, tail_offset plus tail_i
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with block_buffer, tail_i, src_b
        Set tail_i to tail_i plus 1
    End While

    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with block_buffer, tail_bytes, 128
    Let pad_pos be tail_bytes plus 1

    Note: SHA-512 length field is 128 bits (16 bytes), so we need pad_pos <= 112
    If pad_pos is greater than 112:
        Let zero_idx be pad_pos
        While zero_idx is less than 128:
            proc memory_set_byte from Memory with block_buffer, zero_idx, 0
            Set zero_idx to zero_idx plus 1
        End While
        proc sha512_compress_block with state_buffer, block_buffer
        Let z2 be 0
        While z2 is less than 112:
            proc memory_set_byte from Memory with block_buffer, z2, 0
            Set z2 to z2 plus 1
        End While
    Otherwise:
        Let z_inner be pad_pos
        While z_inner is less than 112:
            proc memory_set_byte from Memory with block_buffer, z_inner, 0
            Set z_inner to z_inner plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Note: Append 128-bit length: high 64 bits = 0 (we cannot exceed 2^64 bits),
    Note: low 64 bits = bit-length big-endian.
    Let high_idx be 0
    While high_idx is less than 8:
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with block_buffer, 112 plus high_idx, 0
        Set high_idx to high_idx plus 1
    End While
    Let bit_length be message_length multiplied by 8
    Let bb_i be 7
    While bb_i is greater than 0 minus 1:
        Let byte_value be bit_length modulo by 256
        Set bit_length to bit_length divided by 256
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with block_buffer, 120 plus bb_i, byte_value
        Set bb_i to bb_i minus 1
    End While

    proc sha512_compress_block with state_buffer, block_buffer

    Note: Serialize output bytes from state words (big-endian 64-bit).
    Note: Uses bitwise_and + shr64 to avoid signed-integer division/modulo
    Note: yielding negative values when the state word has the high bit set
    Note: (which happens routinely for SHA-512 since state words are unsigned
    Note: 64-bit but Runa Integer is signed two's complement).
    Let words_to_emit be out_size divided by 8
    Let state_word_index be 0
    While state_word_index is less than words_to_emit:
        Let state_word be proc memory_get_qword from Memory with state_buffer, state_word_index multiplied by 8
        Let byte_idx be 7
        While byte_idx is greater than 0 minus 1:
            Let byte_val be state_word bitwise_and 255
            Set state_word to proc shr64 with state_word, 8
            proc memory_set_byte from Memory with out_digest, state_word_index multiplied by 8 plus byte_idx, byte_val
            Set byte_idx to byte_idx minus 1
        End While
        Set state_word_index to state_word_index plus 1
    End While

    Return out_size
End Process

Process called "sha384_hash" takes arena as Integer, message as Integer, message_length as Integer, out_digest as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    SHA-384 IV per FIPS 180-4 5.3.4: derived from the fractional parts of
    square roots of the 9th-16th primes. Truncated output is the first 48
    of the 64 bytes produced by the SHA-512 core.
    @End Reasoning

    Return proc sha512_hash_with_iv with arena, message, message_length, out_digest, 48, 0 minus 3766243637369245691, 0 minus 7585448692575644857, 0 minus 6126187401202741280, 0 minus 6014050646534375086, 0 minus 5466263437665506918, 0 minus 5292618179101400454, 0 minus 1808691350907881580, 1352829826225912065
End Process

